citeinfo.title: City of Ann Arbor (Building Footprints)

descript.abstract: Woolpert completed a semi-automated method for building generation utilizing new countywide 2009 LiDAR data and existing 2005-2008 orthoimagery. Buildings over 100 square feet were generated and run through a QC process. The final building polygons were developed for the entire ±709-square mile county area. The dataset has had all but those footprints near or within the City of Ann Arbor and contains an average building height.
descript.purpose: The building outline dataset for the City of Ann Arbor.
descript.supplinf: The City of Ann Arbor used the base data for the entire County, excluded all sites outside the City and edited the remaining data.

dataqual.logic: Woolpert generated the building polygons using the 2009 LiDAR dataset.

horizpa.horizpar: In accordance with the specifications of the project, the building polygon dataset produced for this project was consistent across the entire project area, and met the specifications of the county's GIS system. Buildings were captured in a semi-automated method as generalized polygons.
